#: ../../library/argparse.rst:259
msgid "parents"
msgstr "fĂ¶rĂ¤ldrar"

#: ../../library/argparse.rst:261
msgid ""
"Sometimes, several parsers share a common set of arguments. Rather than "
"repeating the definitions of these arguments, a single parser with all the "
"shared arguments and passed to ``parents=`` argument "
"to :class:`ArgumentParser` can be used.  The ``parents=`` argument takes a "
"list of :class:`ArgumentParser` objects, collects all the positional and "
"optional actions from them, and adds these actions to "
"the :class:`ArgumentParser` object being constructed::"
msgstr ""
"Ibland delar flera parsers en gemensam uppsĂ¤ttning argument. IstĂ¤llet fĂ¶r "
"att upprepa definitionerna av dessa argument, kan en enda parser med alla de "
"delade argumenten och som skickas till ``parents=`` argumentet "
"till :class:`ArgumentParser` anvĂ¤ndas.  Argumentet ``parents=`` tar en lista "
"med :class:`ArgumentParser`-objekt, samlar in alla positionella och valfria "
"ĂĄtgĂ¤rder frĂĄn dem och lĂ¤gger till dessa ĂĄtgĂ¤rder "
"till :class:`ArgumentParser`-objektet som konstrueras::"

#: ../../library/argparse.rst:268
